These Operators helps us in performing Bitwise Operations in Java. These work based on the bits. 

1. Bitwise AND (&) -> if both bits 1 then 1 else 0.
2. Bitwise OR (|) -> if atleast one bit 1 then 1 else 0.
3. Bitwise Right Shift (>>) -> shift bits right by right operand times (num * pow(2, n)).
4. Bitwise Left Shift (<<) -> shift bits left by right operand times (num / pow(2, n)).
5. Bitwise XOR (^) -> if both bits same then 0 else 1.
6. Bitwise NOT (~) -> negate bits if 1 then 0 else if 0 then 1 (last bit represents sign).
7. Bitwise Unsigned Right Shift (>>>) --> works same as right shift for (+ve) numbers, but ignores sign bit for (-ve) numbers.